Cell["\<\
Unfortunately, the limit for t\[RightArrow]\[Infinity] does not vanish, but \
gives \[Infinity]. Hence the method of creative telescoping does not enable \
us to do a clean reasoning; a fortiori the same is true for Takayama's \
algorithm (as described in the thesis).\
\>", "Text"],

Cell["\<\
Even if we ignore these problems, the next difficulties arise when comparing \
initial values. When we consider the first derivative w.r.t. z, we encounter \
an integral that does not converge for any n subject to the given conditions:\
\
\>", "Text"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"D", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
      RowBox[{"z", " ", "t"}], "]"}], "/", 
