  "0"}]], "Output"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
This recurrence, together with the observation that the integral is 0 for \
either m or n being 0 (but not both at the same time), immediately implies \
the closed form (-1)^(n + 1)*m!*n!/(m + n)!*BernoulliB[m + n] for m>0 and n>0.\
\>", "Text"],

